HEADWORD: Incorruptness
<hw>In`cor*rupt"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Freedom or
exemption from decay or corruption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Probity; integrity; honesty.</def>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incrassate</ent>⟦br⟧
